```

#### Create Your SSH Config

1. Open or create: `~/.ssh/config`

   ```bash
   nano ~/.ssh/config
   ```

2. Add entries based on the template for each platform host:

   ```
   Host [host1-placeholder]
       HostName [hostname.example.com]
       User [your-username]
       IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
       [Placeholder: additional host-specific settings]

   Host [host2-placeholder]
       HostName [hostname.example.com]
       User [your-username]
       IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
       [Placeholder: additional host-specific settings]
   ```

3. Set correct permissions:

   ```bash
   chmod 600 ~/.ssh/config
   ```

